.B "2nd Release - November 1999"
.BS
[991101]  Enhanced the latex support macros  following  various  contributions
from users.
.BU
[991101]  Added  Favorites  to the  File  pull  down  menu.  This is a  simple
mechanism to allow the user to add a file to a favorites list.
.BU
[991101] Ground up implementation of the regular  expression  pattern matcher,
following licensing problems with the GNU regex. The resultant pattern matcher
is now a little  faster  than GNU regex and is capable of all of the  standard
regular  expression pattern matches. The pattern matcher has diverged from GNU
in that double backslashes are required in the character classes [..] to allow
for escape  sequence  short cuts such as '\\n'  (newline), '\\t' (tab) etc. It
was felt that this compromise was better than having to quote the more obscure
search characters.
.BU
[991101]  Changed  the  hilighting  and  indenting  syntax  to  be  GNU  regex
compliant.
.BU
[991101]   Modified   compare-windows   to  ignore  white  space  by  default,
compare-windows-exact performs an exact character for character comparison.
.BU
[991101]  Enhanced  the tags  support to handle  multiple  tags and  recursive
directory tree searching.
.BU
[991101]  Implemented  osd-help, a gui front end to the on-line help. Required
changes to the help  system  which  gives  macros  access to the on-line  help
buffer, needed for the index and search.
.BU
[991101]  Over-hauled  the  hilighting  scheme files and editor to support the
disabling of buffer hilighting.
.BU
[991101]  Many bugs fixed on all  platforms,  in  particular  unix cutting and
pasting (crashes exceed) and focus problems and NT exit delay.
.BU
[991101] Added tab and newline character printing in buffers.
.BU
[991101] Introduced message line variables "@mx" and "@mxa".
.BU
[991101] New Games - Crossword  cracker. The ideal way to cheat at crosswords.
Uses the  spelling  dictionary  to guess at the word,  given a number of known
letters.
.BU
[991101]  Hook  file  protection   against  globally  bound  keys  -  prevents
re-binding of user defined keys within the macro.
.BU
[991101]  Search/Replace fix for exact mode. Environment  variable search path
fix.
.BU
[991101] hkm4.emf added back into the release (seemed to have gone missing).
.BU
[991101] Cut and paste fix when  running the  \s-1UNIX\s0  version  through an
X-Server such as Exceed in the Windows environment.
.BU
[991101] Plain text printer device added.
.BU
[991101] Obscure OSD fix.
.BU
[991101] New OSD help search facility Menu->Help->General Help.
.BU
[991101] Fix for NT hang-up on shut down (typically encountered when running a
source debugger).
.BU
[991101] Fix for NT process spawning with spaces in the names.
.BU
[991101] Metris macro fix, OSD bug fix, NT display fix.
.BU
[991101] New - color scheme, GVim look.
.BU
[991101] New - Unix/Linux support for Wheel Mouse (mouse.emf).
.BU
[991101]  New - Color  schemes,  Plain;  for  those  that do not  care  for an
abundance of colors.
.BU
[991101]  Modified  the  numeric  key-pad  behavior  to be  consistent  on all
platforms.  Problems were noted with the \s-1UNIX\s0  number lock  orientation
which was reversed.
.BU
[991101] New - Color scheme variables which allow the hkXXX files to determine
the level of hilighting to apply to their templates.
.BU
[991101] Line length fix; more  graceful  behavior  (i.e. does not crash) when
the line length exceeds 64K.
.BU
[991101]  Intercept the windows 105 keyboard  application key (typically right
hand side of keyboard  next to the control key). The key is called  "menu". By
default this is bound in win32.emf,  however users may bind it as a prefix for
their own key combinations in much the same way as "Alt" or "C-x" if required.
.BU
[991101] New; OMG's IDL language template added.
.BU
[991101] Fix for windows short name in next-buffer.
.BE
.B "2nd Release - Beta #1 - May 1999."
.BS
[990501] Bug fixes with multi-language support and spelling dictionaries.
.BU
[990501] Fixed  fill-paragraph such that it retains the cursor position in the
